 H^1=W^{1, 2}(\Omega)\\ V_1=\{ f\in  H^2 (\Omega) : \frac{\partial f}{\partial n}|_{\partial \Omega} =0\}\\ H_2=\{ f\in L^2(\Omega)^2: \nabla . f =0,~ f.n=0 \text{ on } \partial \Omega\}\\ V_2 = \{ f\in H^1_0(\Omega)^2 : \nabla . f =0\} 
C \in L^2(0, \tau ; V_1) \cap L^\infty (0, \tau; H^1)
u \in L^2(0, \tau ; V_2) \cap L^\infty (0, \tau; H_1)
|\cdot|
L^2(\Omega)
l^2(\Omega)^2
\Omega
\mathbb{R^2}
\partial \Omega
 C'_t = d \Delta C - u . \nabla C
M>0
 |\frac{\partial  C}{\partial t}| \leq | d \Delta C| + |u . \nabla C|\qquad \text{ triangle inequality} 
 \leq  d\|\Delta C |  ~+~\|u\|_{L^4(\Omega)^2} \|\nabla C\|_{L^4(\Omega)^2}\qquad\text{How?} 
 \leq  d\|\Delta C | + M |u|^{1/2} \|u\|^{1/2}_{H^1(\Omega)^2} \|C\|^{1/2}_{H^1(\Omega)} \|C\|^{1/2}_{H^2(\Omega)}\qquad\text{How is this for some $M>0$?} 
